.TH l2g 1 "October 1994" "Scilab Group" "Scilab macro"
.so man1/sci.an
.SH NAME 
l2g - graph from an adjacency description
.SH CALLING SEQUENCE
.nf
[g] = l2g(a,lp,ls,dir)
.fi
.SH PARAMETERS
.TP 2
g
: graph list
.TP 2
a
: adjacency matrix
.TP 6
lp,ls
: vectors of the adjacency description, lp is the pointer array and 
  ls is the node array
.TP 4
dir
: integer flag, 1 if the graph is directed, 0 if the graph is 
  undirected
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fVl2g\fR computes a graph list from the adjacency matrix and vectors.
.SH SEE ALSO
l2adj, adj2l
